# Copyrights

## Sift PHP framework

Sift is a fork of symfony 1.0 framework with backports from version 1.4.
symfony is licensed under MIT license. []

Symfony 1.x is originally based on Mojavi3 by Sean Kerr <sean@code-box.org>

## Internalization component

Sift I18n component is based on i18n classes from Prado framework which is license
under modified BSD license. [http://www.pradosoft.com/license/]

## International Components for Unicode

Sift uses CLDR database from CLDR - Unicode Common Locale Data Repository [http://cldr.unicode.org/]
which is licensed under MIT license. See [http://www.unicode.org/copyright.html].

## Mime detection component

Sift uses mime database data from "Shared mime info" project, [http://freedesktop.org/wiki/Software/shared-mime-info]
which is license under GPLv2.

## Hypnenation component

Sift uses hyphenation patterns from hyph-utf8 for TeX. [http://tug.org/tex-hyphen/#introduction]

## Image component

Sift uses code originally written by Stuart Lowes <stuart.lowes@gmail.com> and its contributors.

